name: letter
notes: use if (1) letter contains another element/wrapper OR (2) letter variations are needed; otherwise just use letter block styles

name: sect
notes: for subsections that are part of a deliberate structure. Cf. subhead.

name: title
notes: use for title of any element, including parent sections, sect elements, sidebars, etc.

name: number
notes: use for section head also, i.e. FMH

name: p-cont
notes: use for later part of a single content paragraph interrupted by another element, e.g. a list or extract

name: footnote
notes: use for footnotes containing other elements, e.g. an extract

name: endnote
notes: use for endnotes containing other elements, e.g. an extract

name: subhead
notes: use for headings that are not logically part of a hierarchy

name: delete
notes: use for paragraphs in source file that should be removed from output HTML
